1.Write a Java program that reads a string from the user and convert the input to lowercase to handle uppercase letters. Use a character array to check each character and keep track of the counts. Finally, print the frequency of each vowel. Hint: Use the toCharArray() String method to convert the string into characters. Use toLowerCase() String method to convert the input to lowercase.
 Code:
  import java.util.Scanner;
 public class Vowel {
     public static void main(String[] args) {
         Scanner scan = new Scanner(System.in);
         int count_a = 0, count_e = 0, count_i = 0, count_o = 0, count_u = 0;
         System.out.println("Name: Subasri P");
         System.out.println("Reg no:2024503025");
         System.out.print("Enter the string:");
         String str1 = scan.nextLine();
         String str2 = str1.toLowerCase();
         char[]letters=str2.toCharArray();
 
        for (int i=0;i<str2.length();i++)
         {
             if (letters[i] == 'a')
             {
                 count_a++;
             }
             else if (letters[i] == 'e')
             {
                 count_e++;
             }
             else if (letters[i] == 'i')
             {
                 count_i++;
             }
             else if (letters[i] == 'o')
             {
                 count_o++;
             }
             else if (letters[i] == 'u')
             {
                 count_u++;
             }
             else continue;
         }
         System.out.println("\n TheFrequency of vowel in the given String....");
         System.out.println("a=" + count_a + "times");
         System.out.println("e=" + count_e + "times");
         System.out.println("i=" + count_i + "times");
         System.out.println("o=" + count_o + "times");
         System.out.println("u=" + count_u + "times");
     }
 }
output:
Enter the string:network connecting
The frequency of vowel in the given string....
a=0times
e=1times
i=1times
o=2times
u=0times
